<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-24T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-24T07:00:00-05:00" n="43" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/19690:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-24T14:00:00+02:00">February
                                    24, 1942—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 4:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>144. There has been no reference in Finnish press thus far to Stalin’s
                            declaration yesterday<note n="59" xml:id="d43fn59">The Department
                                received a report of Stalin’s speech in telegram No. 163 of February
                                24, from the Chargé in the Soviet Union, <ref target="frus1942v03#pg_416">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>,
                                    p. 416</ref>.</note> on anniversary of Red Army including his
                            statement that recovery of Baltic States and Karelia is Soviet war
                            aim.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>